 opfor6ammocacheinfo {
  coords 1307.074 7.039 3244.448
  m_sTitle "Ammo and Cache Information"
  m_sTextData "Up to 2x cells plus an HQ section of up to 4-6 men each. Soviet-era small arms. RPGs, other AK variants, bolt-action rifles, and a medic. We have 1x PKM gun and 1x VBIED."\
  ""\
  "AMMO BOX AT SPAWN WITH 5x radios. Use them however you'd like."\
  ""\
  "Our caches have limited extra 7.62 ammo for the bolt-action and AKs which use it, however, if you drop your weapon and fallback, you will only be able to grab an AK-74 and 5.45 magazines. There are limited amounts of grenades at the caches as well, use them wisely. Cache location number 3 also has 2 extra disposable RPGs."\
  ""\
  ""
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "GC_INSURGENT"
  }
  m_iOrder 6
 }
 ALL_First_Tab_overview {
  coords 2098.159 1.336 3117.191
  m_sTitle "Overview"
  m_sTextData "Late 2003, early operations in the Pech River Valley, Kunar Province, Afghanistan. US Army conducts sweeps through the valley, seeking weapons caches and establishing a presence to disrupt insurgent networks."\
  ""\
  "Special thanks to Haesten for his service and for assisting me to make the unit loadouts in this mission as accurate as possible, within reason, based on his own experiences/deployments."\
  ""\
  "Mission created by Gabe"
  m_bEmptyFactionVisibility 1
  m_iOrder 0
 }
 ALL_Last_Tab_endconditions {
  coords 2038.82 18.284 3340.131
  m_sTitle "Notes & End Conditions (MUST READ)"
  m_sTextData "Civilians may NOT wander off into the mountains to have a party of their own separate from the rest of the playerbase. They are expected to exist nearby the other players, roleplaying as civilians making deliveries and/or going about their daily lives. Should they align more with one side than the other, they may provide intel or receive radios to provide intel. They may not become combatants of any kind, however."\
  ""\
  "Insurgents can drop their gear and retreat further back into the AO without being killed. US MUST NOT metagame and kill an unarmed insurgent just because they know which person it is and they know said person is on the enemy team. "\
  ""\
  "GMs should revive insurgents who get executed for no good reason. Attempting to retreat with a weapon in your hand or while wearing a tactical vest IS good reason to be killed, for example, but an insurgent who drops their gun and tactical vest should be assumed to be a civilian. "\
  ""\
  "Civilians wear rucksacks sometimes - a ruck is not an indication of being a combatant."\
  ""\
  "The US Army must successfully sweep and clear at least 4 of the 6 objective areas of insurgents within 60 minutes (excluding 5 minute setup timer). "\
  ""\
  "US Army loses if:"\
  "     - They take 75% casualties"\
  "     - They kill 80% of the player civilians"\
  "     - They fail to complete the objective in time"\
  ""\
  "Insurgents lose if:"\
  "     - They take 90% casualties"\
  "     - US Army completes their objective in time"
  m_bShowForAnyFaction 1
  m_iOrder 8
 }
 opfor4execution {
  coords 3498.168 134.538 4440.773
  m_sTitle "Execution"
  m_sTextData "The infidels have strict rules and will not shoot us if we look like the civilians. Occupy objective areas or surrounding areas in order to engage and delay the enemy US forces."\
  ""\
  "It is recommended that we try to carry as much of our inventory as possible in our shirts and pants to avoid using tactical vests where able in case we need to drop our gear/weapons and fall back. "\
  ""\
  "We can simply pretend to be part of the civilian population, fall back to one of our caches (marked on the map), and re-engage them."\
  ""\
  "Cache location number 3 has a couple extra disposable RPGs, it is suggested that we use the ones we have first before grabbing those since, as mentioned above, we may have to drop our weapons and gear to fall back without being shot at and killed. It would be a shame to lose all our RPGs early on in this fight!"\
  ""\
  ""\
  ""\
  ""
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "GC_INSURGENT"
  }
  m_iOrder 4
 }
 CIVILIAN {
  coords 777.667 77.775 3123.851
  m_sTitle "CIVILIAN BRIEFING"
  m_sTextData "You spawn in pairs, your corresponding group number is marked on the map so you know where you spawn. Only you and your fellow civilians see this. "\
  ""\
  "Mission (required): roleplay as delivery drivers, drug dealers, or whatever your imagination can come up with. Conduct deliveries at each of the zones. Your job is to create a dynamic civilian experience."\
  ""\
  "You may not pick up weapons or grenades of any kind. You MAY, however, choose to lean your allegiances to one side over the other, and provide intel to that side should you have any information to give. "\
  ""\
  "Mission maker's intent is that you choose to do this based on your experience in the game, rather than having any kind of meta-game bias against the players on one team versus the other. If you feel that the insurgents are treating you poorly, turn on them and give up their locations to the Americans. If the Americans treat you poorly, maybe you end up being given a radio by the insurgents and give the insurgents real time strategic information."\
  ""\
  ""
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "CIV"
  }
 }
}